article.headline: Wildcats earn ninth win of the season
article.linkText: Polk sees double-double as Arizona beats Oregon State
article.story:
TUCSON, Ariz. (AP) -- Shawntinice Polk had 18 points and 11
rebounds for her 10th double-double of the season, leading No. 20
Arizona to a 72-44 victory over Oregon State on Saturday.

	   The Wildcats (9-3, 3-1) led by 16 points at the break and built
on that lead with a 16-2 run at the start of the second half.

	   Natalie Jones converted a three-point play and hit a 3-pointer
to give Arizona a 47-19 lead. The Wildcats led by as many as 39
points in the second half.

	   Dee-Dee Wheeler added 15 points, Aimee Grzyb scored 11 and
Krista Warren had 10 for Arizona.

	   Mandy Close led Oregon State with 11 points.

	   Arizona charged to a 10-2 lead in the first six minutes, scored
10 straight points and opened a 24-6 lead with 7:39 left in the
first half.

	   Oregon State (7-6, 1-3) scored the last seven points of the
first half to close within 31-15, but was unable to overcome its 16
turnovers and 28 percent shooting from the field in the first half.

	   Oregon State shot 31 percent for the game. Arizona shot 54
percent.
